title: High school football: Hinsdale South wins third straight
text:
High school football: Hinsdale South wins third straight Published: Friday, Oct. 9, 2015 11:59 p.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
FRANKLIN PARK â€“ Hinsdale South notched its third straight win with a 28-7 victory against Leyden on Oct. 9. 
Marcus Curry opened the scoring with a 12-yard touchdown run and the Hornets (5-2 overall, 4-1 West Suburban Gold) kept the Eagles at bay the rest of the way. 
South hosts Hinsdale Central in a West Suburban Silver crossover game on Oct. 16.
